This paper is about improving neural machine translation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method to guide the distribution of predictions, which involves evaluating the fluency and faithfulness of the generated translations. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper may involve training neural networks, which could place it in sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may involve image-to-text translation, which could place it in sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
